IV	JavaScript
31.	If you want to get out of a while loop, which of the following options would you use?
(A)	exit
(B)	close
(C)	end
(D)	break

 
32.	What will be the result of executing the following code?
function test() {
console.log( a + " and " + foo() );
var a = 1;
function foo() {
return 2;
}
}
test();
(A)	a and foo
(B)	undefined and 2
(C)	1 and 2
(D)	null and 2

33.	Which of the following is the correct way to define a JavaScript array?
(A)	var colors = (1:"red", 2:"green", 3:"blue")
(B)	var colors = "red", "green", "blue"
(C)	var colors = { “1”:”red”,”2”:”green”,”3”,”blue”}
(D)	var colors = ["red", "green", "blue"]

34.	What will be the result of executing the following code:
var people = [
{name: 'ivan', age: 20},
{name: 'pesho', age: 30},
{name: 'gosho', age: 15},
];
var result = people.filter(function( p) {
return p.age > 20;
});
(A)	true
(B)	{name: 'pesho', age: 30}
(C)	[{name: 'pesho', age: 30}]
(D)	65

35.	How would you declare a JavaScript variable?
(A)	var carName;
(B)	variable carName;
(C)	v carName;
(D)	declare carName;

 
36.	How would you check if a is an array in JavaScript?
(A)	isArray(a) === true
(B)	typeof a === 'array'
(C)	Array.isArray(a) === true
(D)	a.isArray() === true

37.	What is the value of a after executing the following code?
var b = null;
var c = false;
var a = (b||c?true:false);
(A)	null
(B)	undefined
(C)	true
(D)	false

38.	In what order will the numbers 1-4 be logged to the console after executing the following code?
(function() {
console.log(1);
setTimeout(function(){console.log(2)}, 1000);
setTimeout(function(){console.log(3)}, 0);
console.log(4);
})();
(A)	1, 4, 3, 2
(B)	1, 2, 3, 4
(C)	1,3, 2, 4
(D)	2, 3, 4, 1

39.	Which of the following is correct?
(A)	for($i=0;$i<4; ) { … }
(B)	for($i=0;$i<4; $i++) { … }
(C)	for( ; ; ) { … }
(D)	All of the above.

40.	How would you create a function in JavaScript?
(A)	function myFunction() { … }
(B)	int myFunction = function() { … }
(C)	function:myFunction() { … }
(D)	var myFunction = function() { … }